    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="607"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5831/232a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sayre</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Swedish Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boström</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-30">March 30,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I am sorry that it was
                    impossible to confer with the President prior to his departure with regard to
                    specific concessions to be granted to Sweden in the present trade agreement
                    negotiations. As a matter of general policy we make it a practice to obtain the
                    President’s approval in such matters prior to discussing the proposed
                    concessions with the representatives of other governments. In this particular
                    instance, however, I understand the necessity for avoiding the loss of time in
                    our negotiations with you, and we have authorized, on that account, our
                    representatives in the negotiations to discuss <pb facs="0816" n="740"
                        xml:id="pg_740"/> with you various possible concessions on Swedish products
                    to be embodied in the trade agreement. I am sure that you understand that these
                    discussions must necessarily be without commitment of any kind, and that
                    whatever proposals may be made on our side will be subject entirely to the
                    President’s approval.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis B. Sayre</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
